<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,752,192,312]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,256,192,217]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,232,193,217]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
–
</emphasis>
Surstylus elongate, basally with 
<emphasis box="[636,661,193,216]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">ca</emphasis>
. 6 long bristles, submedially slightly curved, distally setigerous (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[136,180,2065,2086]" captionTargetBox="[143,1463,1127,2020]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[126,1488,1111,2032]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 5–8. Stegana (Oxyphortica) acutipenis, new species, male genitalia: 5, epandrium and cercus (lateral view); 6, surstylus (frontal view); 7, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view); 8, ditto (lateral view). Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4508945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4508945/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); aedeagus basally round, medially broadened, apically narrowed, slightly sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[448,552,289,312]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[136,180,2065,2086]" captionTargetBox="[143,1463,1127,2020]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[126,1488,1111,2032]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 5–8. Stegana (Oxyphortica) acutipenis, new species, male genitalia: 5, epandrium and cercus (lateral view); 6, surstylus (frontal view); 7, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view); 8, ditto (lateral view). Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4508945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4508945/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Figs. 7, 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,752,352,408]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,272,352,377]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,242,353,377]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Description</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
Only those characters that differ from the species above are given in this description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,752,449,504]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Male. Head: Pedical yellow, with 1 long seta and several minute setulae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,751,545,600]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
Wing: Costal vein between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[427,451,557,571]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[521,545,557,571]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">4+5</subScript>
with 
<emphasis box="[606,631,545,568]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">ca</emphasis>
. 8 peg-like spinules on ventral surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,752,641,696]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Abdomen: All tergites mostly dark brown to black except for second to third tergites yellow along anterior margins.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,752,737,824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
Male terminalia: Epandrium with developed apodeme on anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[306,377,769,792]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[136,180,2065,2086]" captionTargetBox="[143,1463,1127,2020]" captionTargetId="figure-8@2.[126,1488,1111,2032]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 5–8. Stegana (Oxyphortica) acutipenis, new species, male genitalia: 5, epandrium and cercus (lateral view); 6, surstylus (frontal view); 7, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view); 8, ditto (lateral view). Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4508945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4508945/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Gonopod small lobe. Paramere absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,752,865,1048]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
Measurements: BL = 
<quantity box="[362,462,865,888]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.40 mm</quantity>
in 
<typeStatus box="[504,600,865,888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<quantity box="[618,720,865,888]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.05" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="4.05">4.05 mm</quantity>
in 
<typeStatus box="[113,210,897,920]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">paratype</typeStatus>
); ThL = 
<quantity box="[310,407,897,920]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.56" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.56">1.56 mm</quantity>
(1.74); WL = 
<quantity box="[573,670,897,920]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="2.55">2.55 mm</quantity>
(2.95); WW = 
<quantity box="[194,290,929,952]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.18" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.18">1.18 mm</quantity>
(1.42).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,752,865,1048]" lastBlockId="3.[812,1451,193,344]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Indices: arb = 8/6 (8/6), avd = 1.00 (1.00), adf = 2.27 (3.00), flw = 2.00 (2.40), FW/HW = 0.37 (0.36), ch/o = 0.07 (0.06), prorb = 1.17 (0.89), rcorb = 0.60 (0.66), vb = 0.45 (0.48), dcl = 0.46 (0.46), sctl = 1.05 (1.15), sterno = 0.73 (0.60), orbito = 2.00 (1.60), dcp = 0.27 (0.28), presctl = 0.55 (0.55), sctlp = 0.84 (0.93), C = 2.60 (3.12), 4c = 0.79 (0.77), 4v = 1.55 (1.84), 5x = 1.42 (1.46), ac = 6.00 (4.92), M = 0.45 (0.49), C3F = 1.00 (1.00).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[812,1451,384,440]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,958,384,409]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,936,385,409]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</emphasis>
–
</emphasis>
A combination of the Latin words: “acutus” and “penis”, referring to the apically acute aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[812,1163,480,505]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" type="distribution">
